div.p:
THE Pores of the Skin receive touch, as the Eye light, the Eare sound, the


                  Nose scent, the Tongue tast. Thus the Spirits passe, and repasse by the holes, they peirce through the dull Matter, carrying their severall Burthens out, & in, yet it is neither the Burthen, nor the Passage that makes the different Sense, but the different Motion;

                     To prove that it is the several Motion, is, that wee shall have the same sense in our sleep, either to move Pleasure, or feele Paine. for if the Motion that comes through the Pores of the Skin, were as the Motions that come from the Eye, Eare, Nose, Mouth, then the Body might receive Sound, Light, Scent, Tast, all over as it doth Touch.
